redkoffee aka Clarisse Prévost pays tribute to sci-fi love story Kaiba created by Masaki Yuasa in 2008. In this world, memories can be turned into data and stored. Even if the body dies, its memories live on, and can be transferred to another body. Bad memories can be erased, and good ones downloaded. However, this is something only the privileged can do. In a world like this, our protagonist, Kaiba, is traveling in another body with no memories of his own..

Japanese-American composer, poet, lyricist, singer and multi-instrumentalist Ayuo Takahashi shares music from a life-long interest in the sonic similarities between medieval Western celtic music and the musical traditions of Asia.

Monthly enqiuries into encounters in harmony, forms of hearing, and occasionally responding.
From the host: "A sonic continuation of TWICE BITTEN, the surreal showcase and theatre show presented by Neoprene Genie at Southbank Centre. Featuring live and exclusive performances from BODUR, XT1ANA, KMNC and Tice Cin alongside newly curated recordings from the likes of Meron T, Asmaa Jama and Chantel Foo. With soundscapes by Ikonika, Tice, KMNC and more. TWICE BITTEN. ONCE MORE? asks how do we respond to and evolve in an ever harshening world. Ambient, experimental, BPM pushing and simultaneously traditional, a settling of sounds from beyond the vine."

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
